In a blender, whirl ginger and 1 cup water until pureed. Pour mixture into a medium saucepan with pineapple juice and 1/4 cup sugar. Stir often over high heat until simmering, 6 to 8 minutes. Ladle about 1 cup juice mixture into a blender. Add mango and whirl until pureed. Return to pan. Set a fine strainer over a heatproof pitcher. Ladle punch mixture into strainer, stirring to press out liquid. Discard pulp. Taste punch; add more sugar if you like. Serve hot or cold in mugs or glasses.